</blockquote>
<p>A good suggestion. We can look into that. - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lurkd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1500566); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1500566&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1597877609" alt="LurkD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1500566)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lurkd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1500566); return false;">LurkD</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>I would like a definition page for the different tags. Tags like &quot;sentient&quot; or &quot;humanoid&quot; are easy enough to understand, but &quot;ectoentropic&quot; and a few others are a bit more confusing. Maybe someone could come up with a page that defines the different tags, along with linking to the list of articles that have that tag.</li>
<li>Contextual links expanded</li>
<li>&quot;define keter and euclid so that it becomes less confusing for people writeing article for the first time&quot;</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>Consider the following: <a href="http://05command.wikidot.com/tag-guide">http://05command.wikidot.com/tag-guide</a> - <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lurkd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1500566); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1500566&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1597877609" alt="LurkD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1500566)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/lurkd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1500566); return false;">LurkD</a></span></p>
<blockquote>
